A fisherman at Scottburgh beach collapsed and died while on a fishing trip with his brother. Captain Adam Francis, Scottburgh SAPS communications officer, confirmed the tragic demise of the man. He said that a report was filed with Scottburgh SAPS after the fisherman collapsed and died at the beach. “It is alleged by the deceased brother that they were fishing at Scottburgh beach. At one stage he noticed his brother sitting down and thereafter his brother collapsed. He was certified dead on the beach by paramedics,” Francis said. The body was removed from the beach by a private funeral parlour for the family.